fields.name: special_time

fields.name: state

fields.name: async
fields.description: If set to C(true) Yum will download packages and metadata from this repo in parallel, if possible.

fields.name: bandwidth
fields.description: Maximum available network bandwidth in bytes/second. Used with the I(throttle) option.

fields.name: baseurl

fields.name: cost
fields.description: Relative cost of accessing this repository. Useful for weighing one repos packages as greater/less than any other.

fields.name: deltarpm_metadata_percentage
fields.description: When the relative size of deltarpm metadata vs pkgs is larger than this, deltarpm metadata is not downloaded from the repo. Note that you can give values over C(100), so C(200) means that the metadata is required to be half the size of the packages. Use C(0) to turn off this check, and always download metadata.

fields.name: deltarpm_percentage
fields.description: When the relative size of delta vs pkg is larger than this, delta is not used. Use C(0) to turn off delta rpm processing. Local repositories (with file:// I(baseurl)) have delta rpms turned off by default.

fields.name: description

fields.name: enabled
fields.description: This tells yum whether or not use this repository.

fields.name: enablegroups
fields.description: Determines whether yum will allow the use of package groups for this repository.

fields.name: exclude
fields.description: List of packages to exclude from updates or installs. This should be a space separated list. Shell globs using wildcards (eg. C(*) and C(?)) are allowed.

fields.name: failovermethod
fields.description: C(roundrobin) randomly selects a URL out of the list of URLs to start with and proceeds through each of them as it encounters a failure contacting the host.

fields.name: file
fields.description: File name without the C(.repo) extension to save the repo in. Defaults to the value of I(name).

fields.name: gpgcakey
fields.description: A URL pointing to the ASCII-armored CA key file for the repository.

fields.name: gpgcheck
fields.description: Tells yum whether or not it should perform a GPG signature check on packages.

fields.name: gpgkey
fields.description: A URL pointing to the ASCII-armored GPG key file for the repository.

fields.name: module_hotfixes
fields.description: Disable module RPM filtering and make all RPMs from the repository available. The default is C(None).

fields.name: http_caching
fields.description: Determines how upstream HTTP caches are instructed to handle any HTTP downloads that Yum does.

fields.name: include
fields.description: Include external configuration file. Both, local path and URL is supported. Configuration file will be inserted at the position of the I(include=) line. Included files may contain further include lines. Yum will abort with an error if an inclusion loop is detected.

fields.name: includepkgs
fields.description: List of packages you want to only use from a repository. This should be a space separated list. Shell globs using wildcards (eg. C(*) and C(?)) are allowed. Substitution variables (e.g. C($releasever)) are honored here.

fields.name: ip_resolve
fields.description: Determines how yum resolves host names.

fields.name: keepalive
fields.description: This tells yum whether or not HTTP/1.1 keepalive should be used with this repository. This can improve transfer speeds by using one connection when downloading multiple files from a repository.

fields.name: keepcache
fields.description: Either C(1) or C(0). Determines whether or not yum keeps the cache of headers and packages after successful installation.

fields.name: metadata_expire
fields.description: Time (in seconds) after which the metadata will expire.

fields.name: metadata_expire_filter
fields.description: Filter the I(metadata_expire) time, allowing a trade of speed for accuracy if a command doesnt require it. Each yum command can specify that it requires a certain level of timeliness quality from the remote repos. from "Im about to install/upgrade, so this better be current" to "Anything thats available is good enough".

fields.name: metalink
fields.description: Specifies a URL to a metalink file for the repomd.xml, a list of mirrors for the entire repository are generated by converting the mirrors for the repomd.xml file to a I(baseurl).

fields.name: mirrorlist
fields.description: Specifies a URL to a file containing a list of baseurls.

fields.name: mirrorlist_expire
fields.description: Time (in seconds) after which the mirrorlist locally cached will expire.

fields.name: name

fields.name: password

fields.name: priority
fields.description: Enforce ordered protection of repositories. The value is an integer from 1 to 99.

fields.name: protect

fields.name: proxy

fields.name: proxy_password
fields.description: Password for this proxy.

fields.name: proxy_username
fields.description: Username to use for proxy.

fields.name: repo_gpgcheck

fields.name: reposdir

fields.name: retries
fields.description: Set the number of times any attempt to retrieve a file should retry before returning an error. Setting this to C(0) makes yum try forever.

fields.name: s3_enabled
fields.description: Enables support for S3 repositories.

fields.name: skip_if_unavailable
fields.description: If set to C(true) yum will continue running if this repository cannot be contacted for any reason. This should be set carefully as all repos are consulted for any given command.

fields.name: ssl_check_cert_permissions
fields.description: Whether yum should check the permissions on the paths for the certificates on the repository (both remote and local).

fields.name: sslcacert
fields.description: Path to the directory containing the databases of the certificate authorities yum should use to verify SSL certificates.

fields.name: sslclientcert
fields.description: Path to the SSL client certificate yum should use to connect to repos/remote sites.

fields.name: sslclientkey
fields.description: Path to the SSL client key yum should use to connect to repos/remote sites.

fields.name: sslverify
fields.description: Defines whether yum should verify SSL certificates/hosts at all.

fields.name: throttle

fields.name: timeout
fields.description: Number of seconds to wait for a connection before timing out.

fields.name: username

fields.name: attributes

fields.description: Amount of retries if the cache update fails. Also see I(update_cache_retry_max_delay).

fields.name: validate_certs

fields.description: Override the distribution codename to use for PPA repositories. Should usually only be set when working with a PPA on a non-Ubuntu target (for example, Debian or Mint).
